The amount of change for the selected interaction between residues i and j is determined by the ratio between the corresponding FN ij and FP ij frequencies. A value greater than one means this interaction energy has to be decreased, while the opposite indicates this interaction energy has to be increased. We do this by changing the interaction potentials ESS86(i,j) and ESB(i,j) according to 
(9)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
